The Tanzanian Fair Competition Commission has granted its approval for OreCorp Tanzania to increase its interest in Nyanzaga Mining to 51%. This move remains subject to: In addition, members of the OreCorp Group have now entered into a completion agreement with Acacia Mining and other members of the Acacia Group to allow OreCorp Tanzania to move to 100% ownership of NMCL, and thereby 100% ownership of the Nyanzaga Gold Project. This move remains subject to: Following completion Acacia will retain a net smelter return production royalty over the project, capped at US$15 million. Both OreCorp and Acacia believe that a simplified ownership structure of NMCL is beneficial to the future development of the project and would enable it to be best placed to provide significant benefits to Tanzania and all stakeholders.